MAJOR #TBT!!! This is one of the ALDC’s best numbers & most controversial. The 1998 original work went on to be undefeated. The concept 
was taken right from the headlines - young women leaving their newborn babies in a box outside the police station or hospital or even in a public bathroom. Almost a decade later, in 2007 I felt the need to revive it because this horribly sad situation was still going on in our society! Once again this piece went on to cause controversy, open chat rooms, be on top winning, undefeated all over again! 

I always thought I would use it again on the very last episode of Dance Moms. 

This should’ve been the original cast of #dancemoms moms! There mothers were all kind of crazy in their own unique way! Can you spot any #aldcalumni?! Comment below!!!

Thank you @rachel.kreiling original cast!!! !’m Searching for a good clear copy of a 1998 performance!

HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO MY MOM!!! MARYEN LORRAIN MILLER was a pioneer! Starting her very own business in 1945 right after WW11! She supported her family, teaching dance, creating many working employable dancers. They performed with the Rat Pack & Elvis Presley, shot movies and commercials on Miami Beach and she expanded to 7 different studios in the Miami area! She taught children to LOVE the art of DANCE! Kind, Caring, Catholic,  Creative and Classy describe my mom! I know she’s watching over me every moment of every day!
